    "department": "Product",
    "description": "Mirage is an AI-native video platform that intelligently orchestrates production and editing through natural language. Our models leverage contextual awareness to execute the same creative decisions a professional editor would — dramatically improving productivity for experienced teams, while making video creation accessible to anyone.\n\nWe’re an interdisciplinary team addressing some of the most difficult technical and creative challenges in generative media. As an early member of our team, you’ll tackle foundational problems that remain largely unsolved across the industry, driving an outsized impact on the future of creative expression.\n\n\nMore about us\n\nProduct https://mirage.app/captions (Captions by Mirage)\n\nResearch https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.08279 (Seeing Voices, technical-white-paper)\n\nUpdates https://x.com/trymirage (Mirage on X / twitter)\n\nTechCrunch https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/24/mirage-raises-75m-to-continue-building-models-for-its-ai-video-editing-app-captions/, Forbes AI 50 https://www.forbes.com/companies/captions/?list=ai50, Fast Company https://www.fastcompany.com/91270234/video-most-innovative-companies-fast-company-2025-youtube-roku-tubi-vimeo-captions-descript-cour-procreate-synthesia-beeble (press)\n\n\nOur Investors\n\nWe’re very fortunate to have some the best investors and entrepreneurs backing us, including Index Ventures, Kleiner Perkins, Sequoia Capital, Andreessen Horowitz, General Catalyst, Uncommon Projects, Kevin Systrom, Mike Krieger, Lenny Rachitsky, Antoine Martin, Julie Zhuo, Ben Rubin, Jaren Glover, SVAngel, 20VC, Ludlow Ventures, Chapter One, and more.\n\nPlease note that all of our roles will require you to be in-person at our NYC HQ (located in Union Square)\n\nLocation: New York City\n\nDuration: ~8–10 weeks (Summer 2026)\n\nHourly Rate: $50/hour\n\nExpected Graduation Date: Winter 2026 to Summer 2027, we are only seeking undergraduate candidates at this time\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re looking for two Product Design Interns to join our team in the heart of NYC for Summer 2026. This isn’t a “sit back and watch” internship - you’re joining us at the frontier of AI to help simplify video creation and make it accessible to everyone, everywhere.\n\n\nAt our scale, you won’t just shadow, you will own the end to end design process for features that ship to real users. You’ll spend your summer in the room where it happens, collaborating deeply with engineering and product peers to translate complex AI capabilities into high-fidelity, intuitive experiences.\n\nThis is an in-person internship based in our New York City office (Union Square). Please note that we do not provide relocation assistance or housing support for the duration of the program.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Full Stack Design: Work as an integral member of the design team, contributing to core product work and ongoing initiatives\n\n - Prototyping \u0026 Craft: Help build comprehensive user flows, wireframes, and high fidelity prototypes, ensuring execution aligns with our brand and design systems\n\n - Project Ownership: Lead a major project from conception → execution → final presentation, owning the end-to-end process from discovery to engineering handoff.\n\n - Collaborative Iteration: Participate in weekly design critiques and team meetings, gaining experience in incorporating fast paced feedback and iterative design.\n\n - Strategic Design: Articulate the “why” behind your work, learning to balance user needs with technical constraints and business goals\n\n\nABOUT YOU\n\n - Education: Currently pursuing an undergrad degree in Design, HCI, Computer Science or a design-related field with graduation between December 2026 and Summer 2027.\n\n - Design Proficiency: Advanced knowledge of Figma for design and prototyping. Familiarity with AI-assisted design and building tools is a significant plus.\n\n - Strong Portfolio: A portfolio showcasing previous internship work, class projects, or self-initiated case studies that demonstrate clear system thinking and UI/UX skills.\n\n - Product Thinking: Deep curiosity about how products are built from idea to launch and an ability to navigate complex user journeys.\n\n - Communication: Excellent verbal and written skills to discuss, present, and document design decisions.\n\n - Growth Mindset: A high level of ownership and hunger to learn quickly within a highly collaborative, fast moving team.\n\n\nHOW TO APPLY\n\nPlease apply directly on our careers page and complete the application form with your most up-to-date information. A link to your design portfolio is required for consideration.\n\n\nBENEFITS:\n\n - Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision plans\n\n - 401K with employer match\n\n - Commuter Benefits\n\n - Catered lunch multiple days per week\n\n - Dinner stipend every night if you're working late and want a bite!\n\n - Grubhub subscription\n\n - Health \u0026 Wellness Perks\n\n - Multiple team offsites per year with team events every month\n\n - Generous PTO policy\n\nCaptions provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws.\n\nPlease note benefits apply to full time employees only.",
